# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Rust / Cargo
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Build output for every board (boards/*/target, plus any future
# workspace-level target/) — never commit compiled artifacts.
target/

# rustfmt backup files
**/*.rs.bk

# NOTE: Cargo.lock is intentionally NOT listed here. Every board builds a
# binary (firmware/app), not a library, so its Cargo.lock should be
# committed — that's what makes `just build <board>` reproducible
# bit-for-bit between developers and CI. Generic Rust .gitignore templates
# often ignore Cargo.lock; that guidance is for library crates only.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Embedded build/debug artifacts
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.coredump
*.gdb_history
.gdbinit.local
*.log

# Stray firmware images if someone manually copies output to the repo
# root instead of leaving it in target/. If you deliberately want to
# commit a release artifact somewhere (e.g. a /releases dir), carve out
# an exception: `!releases/*.uf2`.
/*.elf
/*.bin
/*.hex
/*.uf2

# NOTE: memory.x, link.x, and other linker-script files ARE source files
# for these boards, not build output — don't add `*.x` or `*.ld` here.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Docker / Compose
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Personal local overrides / secrets for docker compose. Keep an
# .env.example committed, never the real .env.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# CI-only cargo cache bind mount (see docker-compose.ci.yml) — a local
# cache directory, not part of the repo.
.ci-cache/
.cargo-home/

# NOTE: docker-compose.override.yml IS committed in this repo — it's the
# shared USB/--privileged config every developer needs, not a personal
# override. Most Docker .gitignore templates ignore *.override.yml by
# convention; don't copy that rule here.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Editors / IDEs — personal state only, never shared config
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
.zed/
.cursor/
.claude/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# NOTE: boards/*/.cargo/config.toml IS committed — it's the probe-rs/
# espflash runner config every developer needs. Do not add a blanket
# `.cargo/` ignore rule, or you'll exclude this by accident.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Local scratch (not part of the shared repo)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
tmp/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS cruft
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Secrets — e.g. the SSH key used by `just deploy-rpi`
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.pem
id_rsa
id_ed25519
*.p12
